# Banned Patterns — Never Do These

## Never
- `process.env.ANYTHING` outside of `apps/backend/src/config/env.ts`
- Raw `fetch()` or `axios` calls outside of `AzureDevOpsClient`
- Hardcoded Azure DevOps org name, namespace IDs, or permission bitmask numbers inline
- `any` TypeScript type — use `unknown` + Zod
- `.cursorrules` file (deprecated) — use `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` only
- `npm install` or `yarn add` — always `bun add`
- Hardcoded default project name — project is always selected by the user at runtime
- Inline `nodeTypes` or `edgeTypes` objects inside a React component render — causes react-flow to remount nodes on every render
- `localStorage` or `sessionStorage` — not needed, state lives in Zustand + React Query
- Nested ternaries in JSX — extract to a variable or early return
- Catching errors and returning `null` silently — always propagate or log with context

## Environment & Config
- There is NO `AZURE_DEVOPS_DEFAULT_PROJECT` environment variable in this project
- Project selection is a runtime user action, not a config value
- All optional config has sensible defaults defined in the Zod schema in `env.ts`

## API Design
- No endpoint returns raw AzDO API response shapes — always transform to internal types
- Never expose PAT token in any response or log line
- All endpoints require explicit `?project=` param where applicable — no implicit defaults